---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="SEO & AI discovery"
  description="How Amino Brief is built for search engines and AI crawlers — schema, llms.txt, clusters, backlinks."
>
  <Header slot="header" />
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">Growth systems</p>
      <h1>SEO, backlinks, AI crawlers</h1>
      <p>
        We studied what high-performing peptide education sites do structurally (schema, topical clusters, FAQ,
        E-E-A-T) and implemented the same <em>systems</em> with original Amino Brief content — not scraped copy.
      </p>

      <h2>On-site (shipped)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><code>/sitemap-index.xml</code> + per-page lastmod via Astro sitemap</li>
        <li><code>/rss.xml</code> for guides</li>
        <li><code>/llms.txt</code> + <code>/llms-full.txt</code> for AI crawlers</li>
        <li>JSON-LD: Organization, WebSite, Article, Product, FAQPage where relevant</li>
        <li>Evidence badges + author/publisher entity on guides</li>
        <li>Compound cluster hubs at <a href="/compounds">/compounds</a></li>
        <li><a href="/editorial">Editorial standards</a> (E-E-A-T / corrections)</li>
        <li>Internal links: Learn → Compounds → Guides → Tools → Shop accessories</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Backlink strategy (ops, not spam)</h2>
      <p>
        Live tracker: <a href="/outreach">/outreach</a>. Pitch original literacy pieces — no PBN junk.
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li>Pitch original explainers (COA literacy, evidence tiers, sourcing checklist) to wellness editors as citations</li>
        <li>Guest data: publish unique reconstitution math explainers others can link</li>
        <li>Resource page outreach: university lab safety / compounding literacy lists</li>
        <li>Podcast / newsletter swaps with research-literacy creators (disclose relationships)</li>
        <li>Never buy PBNs or fake medical citations</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>AI crawler play</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Clean extractable answers in FAQ blocks (150–250 words)</li>
        <li>Stable canonical URLs; no cloaking</li>
        <li><code>llms.txt</code> points machines at pillars first</li>
        <li>Update dates on revised guides</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Benchmarks we mirrored (structure only)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Peptides Academy — tools + filterable education</li>
        <li>Peptide Research USA — research-framed posts + library</li>
        <li>Industry SEO playbooks — Product/FAQ/Article schema + clusters</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
